OL,4,CClergy speak out over 'racism in Church
OL,5,Cof England'
OL,6, Some ethnic minority staff who made
OL,7, complaints of racism within the Church
OL,8, of England have been paid off to "buy
OL,9, their silence", BBC Panorama has been
OL,10, told.
OL,12,FDr Elizabeth Henry, the Church's former
OL,13,Fadviser on race relations, said some of
OL,14,Fthose who received compensation had had
OL,15,Fto sign non-disclosure agreements.
OL,17,FSome clergy have told Panorama about
OL,18,Fthe racism they have suffered.
OL,20,FThe Church of England is set to publish
OL,21,Fplans promising to address racism.
